Class CircuitColumn

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.control.TableColumnBase<S,T>
      • javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Circuit,java.lang.String>
        • rd.dev.simulation.custom.CircuitColumn
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget

    public class CircuitColumn
extends javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<Circuit,java.lang.String>
    A CircuitGraphicsColumn contains the additional information needed to display a switchable graphic and to select the data item for display The data items delivered to the parent TableView for display in its cells are always strings; the type conversion is handled by the Circuit class. TODO parameterise Circuit so we can re-use for other data models

    • Constructor Detail

      • CircuitColumn

        CircuitColumn(Circuit.Selector selector)
        Produces a column to be displayed in a Circuit table(TableView<Circuit,String>), whose value is a fixed field in a Circuit bean that is chosen by the selector enum. Use the enum to set the header text and graphic, and prepare the column header so its graphic is switchable.
        Parameters:
        selector - an enum specifying which field to display

      • CircuitColumn

        CircuitColumn(java.lang.String productiveStockName)
        Produces a column to be displayed in a Circuit table(TableView<Circuit,String>), whose value is a Stock field referenced by a foreign key in a Circuit bean. The magnitude is selected by the useValueName of the Stock. Use Stock itself to set the header text and graphic, and prepare the column header so its graphic is switchable.
        Parameters:
        productiveStockName - an enum specifying which productive Stock to display
